<p>Maintaining proper star flow is a complex problem, and chances are
that ShareALot.org will from time to time need to change it's
policies for creating, or destroying stars.  These policies have one
goal: enabling users to share their skills and time as effortlessly
as possible.  We face several challenges in this task:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Having too few stars on average in
	accounts can make large transactions difficult or impossible</li>
	<li>Having too many stars on average
	in accounts can lead to artificial inflation of service rates</li>
	<li>Changes in star policy need to fairly affect everyone fairly.</li>
</ul>
<p>Here we describe our initial policy.  We will try to announce any
change in policy well in advance to allow time for feedback on the
new policy.</p>
<ul>
	<li>New users have an initial balance of 0 stars</li>
	<li>To maintain an average of 1000 stars per account, we donate 1000 stars to participating
	charities new account activated.  Charities start out with 1000 stars.</li>
	<li>Users are only activated once a charity pays a user some stars.</li>
</ul>
